core, up to and including many of the publications in the GRIP/GISP2
compendium volume of the Journal of Geophysical Research. This timescale
was created by combining the original layer-counted timescale of Meese and
others (1994), to about 50,000 years, with a timescale constructed using
trace gas measurements from the Vostok and GISP2 cores, placed on the
SPECMAP marine timescale.  See Bender et al. (1994) for details.

IMPORTANT NOTE: for most of the GISP2 files on this CDROM, we have used
this timescale.  Some files were submitted with a timescale provided: in
general, these are the Meese/Sowers timescale but there may be some
discrepancies. Please refer to the document: 'A note on the timescales'
for more information.
